b'@encodelp @BayAreaBiotechI @gcbioinv PK for ARV110 looked rough too at least at the time of 140 mg data. Expectations were way too high for $ARVN - not at efficacious dose but seems their getting there. Think $EPIX is in strong position with 200 mg starting dose. In efficacious range and should get to 400 mg quick'

b'@BayAreaBiotechI @gcbioinv $ARVN valuation has always had the "platform" premium.  mCRPC/110 was only part of the story, as evidenced by recent spike after data in breast/471. $EPIX single-asset, pure-play mCRPC, so success in Ph1 is critical. Agree 7386 has combo & potentially safety advantages over 110'

b'@BayAreaBiotechI @gcbioinv Curious what market expectations are for PSA50 in Ph1 for EPI-7386. In May $ARVN Ph1/2 w ARV110 (140mg+) had ~20% mCRPC patients achieve PSA50 & stock nosedived. Safety was also an issue for ARV110, but suspect 7386 needs to beat these PSA50 to get market buy-in $EPIX'

b'@gcbioinv @BayAreaBiotechI Is luck AND skill an option?!\n\nAgree w/ the good Dr. That plus Pfizer/Myovant deal helps. Recall $PFE led last $EPIX financing. So obviously they remain very dedicated to prostate cancer and are likely acquirer if 7386 works. PC assets scarce imho - $JNJ and $BAYRY lurking too'
b'$EPIX +100% (Nov.-Dec.) into phase 1 EPI-7386 prostate cancer data 1H21.\n\nWhat say you #biotwitter: luck/random/macro or skill/pattern/repeatable? https://t.co/Lywl2aA4ND'
